
[groups]
Text
Totals
Mathematica
Date
Other
Time
DB access

[COUNT]
1
Return number of records in form.
Parameters: form name - text
Result: number
Example: COUNT('Services')

[SUM]
1
Calculates the total of the field.
Parameters: form name - text, field name - text
Result: number
Exampe: SUM('Services', 'Amount')

[LENGTH]
0
Return text length.
Parameters: text
Result: number
Exampe: LENGTH('Ivanov'). Result: 6

[CUT]
0
Return part of text. If the "length" exceeds the length of the text, the text will be cut to the last character.
Parameters: text, begin - number, length - number
Result: text
Exampe: CUT('Ivanov', 4, 3). Result: nov.

[FIND]
0
Returns the starting position of the text.
Parameters: search text, text, begin - number
Result: number
Exampe: FIND('world', 'Hello, world!!!', 1). Result: 8

[REPLACE]
0
Replaces the found part of the text replacement text.
Parameters: text, search text, replacement text.
Result: text
Exampe: REPLACE('Hello, WORLD!!!', 'WORLD', 'FRIEND'). Result: HELLO, FRIEND!!!

[REPLACEALL]
0
Replaces all found the text replacement text.
Parameters: text, search text, replacement text.
Result: text
Exampe: REPLACEALL('---+++---+++---', '+++', '|'). Result: ---|---|---

[UPPER]
0
Returns the text of all the letters, whose uppercase.
Parameters: text
Result: text
Exampe: UPPER('Hello, World!!!'). Result: HELLO, WORLD!!!

[LOWER]
0
Returns the text of all the letters, whose lowercase.
Parameters: text
Result: text
Exampe: LOWER('Hello, WORLD!!!'). Result: hello, world!!!

[TOWORDS]
0
NOT IMPLEMENTED! Returns the number of words. The fractional part is ignored.
Parameters: number
Result: text
Exampe: TOWORDS(1823).

[RURTOWORDS]
0
NOT IMPLEMENTED! Returns the number of words in rubles.
Parameters: number
Result: text
Exampe: RURTOWORDS(1823.23). 

[FUPPER]
0
Returns the text, all the letters that lowercase, and the first title.
Parameters: number
Result: text
Exampe: FUPPER('HELLO, World!!!'). Result: Hello, world!!!

[ROUND]
2
Returns a number rounded to the specified precision.
Parameters: number, the number of decimal places
Result: number
Exampe: ROUND(234.69, 1). Result: 234.7

[TRUNC]
2
Returns the integer part of the number.
Parameters: number
Result: number
Exampe: TRUNC(234.69). Result: 234

[FRAC]
2
Returns the fractional part.
Parameters: number
Result: number
Exampe: FRAC(234.69). Result: 69

[POWER]
2
Raises a number to a power.
Parameters: number, power - number
Result: number
Exampe: POWER(2, 3). Result: 8

[DATE]
3
Return current date.
Parameters: none
Result: date
Exampe: DATE()

[TIME]
5
Return current time.
Parameters: нет
Result: time
Exampe: TIME()

[YEARSBETWEEN]
3
Specifies the interval between dates in years.
Parameters: date1, date2
Result: number
Exampe: YEARSBETWEEN([Begin date], [End date])

[MONTHSBETWEEN]
3
Specifies the interval between the dates in months.
Parameters: date1, date2
Result: number
Exampe: MONTHSBETWEEN([Begin date], [End date])

[DAYSBETWEEN]
3
Specifies the interval between dates in days.
Parameters: date1, date2
Result: number
Exampe: DAYSBETWEEN([Begin date], [End date])

[DAYOF]
3
Extracts from the date of number of day.
Parameters: date
Result: number
Exampe: DAYOF('23.12.15'). Result: 23

[MONTHOF]
3
Extracts from the date of the month.
Parameters: date
Result: number
Exampe: MONTHOF('23.12.15'). Result: 12

[YEAROF]
3
Extracts from the date of number of year.
Parameters: date
Result: number
Exampe: YEAROF('23.12.15'). Result: 15

[WEEKOF]
3
Extracts from the date of the week number of the year.
Parameters: date
Result: number
Exampe: WEEKOF('23.12.15'). 

[WEEKDAY]
3
Determined by the date weekday name.
Parameters: date
Result: text
Exampe: WEEKDAY('23.12.15'). Result: Wednesday

[WEEKDAYBRIEF]
3
Determined by the date weekday name brief.
Parameters: date
Result: text
Exampe: WEEKDAYBRIEF('23.12.15'). Result: Wed

[MONTH]
3
Determines the name of the month to date.
Parameters: date
Result: text
Exampe: MONTH('23.12.15'). Result: December

[MONTHBRIEF]
3
Determines the name of the month to date brief.
Parameters: date
Result: text
Exampe: MONTHBRIEF('23.12.15'). Result: Dec

[NULL]
4
Undefined value.
Parameters: none
Result: NULL
Exampe: NULL()

[IIF]
4
If the first set to TRUE, returns the second value, otherwise it returns the third.
Parameters: Condition, Value1 - any, Value2 - any
Result: any
Exampe: IIF([Amount] > 0, [Amount], '-')
In this example, if a certain amount greater than 0, the value of this sum is written, otherwise, a dash.

[DAYOFWEEK]
3
Extracts from the date of number of the day of the week.
Parameters: date
Result: number
Exampe: DAYOFWEEK('23.12.15'). Result: 3

[RECNO]
4
Determines the number of the current record form.
Parameters: form name - text
Result: number
Example: RECNO('Peoples'). Result: 4

[SUMIF]
1
Calculates the total of the field.
Parameters: form name - text, field name - text, condition - text
Result: number
Exampe: SUMIF('Services', 'Amount', '[completed]=1')

[COUNTIF]
1
Return number of records in form.
Parameters: form name - text, condition - text
Result: number
Example: COUNTIF('Services', '[completed]=1')

[ROUNDTO]
0
Returns a number rounded to the specified precision, adding zeros.
Parameters: number, the number of decimal places
Result: text
Exampe: ROUNDTO(234.69, 2). Result: 234.70

[MAX]
1
Calculates the maximum value.
Parameters: form name - text, field name - text
Result: number
Example: MAX('Services', 'Price')

[MAXIF]
1
Calculates the maximum value.
Parameters: form name - text, field name - text, condition - text
Result: number
Example: MAXIF('Services', 'Price', '[completed]=1')

[MIN]
1
Calculates the minimum value.
Parameters: form name - text, field name - text
Result: number
Example: MIN('Services', 'Price')

[MINIF]
1
Calculates the minimum value.
Parameters: form name - text, field name - text, condition - text
Result: number
Example: MINIF('Services', 'Price', '[completed]=1')

[AVG]
1
Calculates the average value.
Parameters: form name - text, field name - text
Result: number
Example: AVG('Services', 'Price')

[AVGIF]
1
Calculates the average value.
Parameters: form name - text, field name - text, condition - text
Result: number
Example: AVGIF('Services', 'Price', '[completed]=1')

[CSTR]
4
Converts a value to text.
Parameters: value - number, date, time
Result: text
Example: 'Current date: ' + CSTR([date])

[CNUM]
4
Converts a text to number.
Parameters: text
Result: number
Example: [price] * CNUM([text])

[CDATE]
4
Converts a text to date.
Parameters: text
Result: date
Example: MONTHSBETWEEN([date], CDATE('12.10.2013'))

[ADDDAY]
3
Adds / subtracts from the date specified number of days.
Parameters: date, number
Result: date
Example: ADDDAY([date], 8) or ADDDAY([date], -3)

[ADDWEEK]
3
Adds / subtracts from the date specified number of weeks.
Parameters: date, number
Result: date
Example: ADDWEEK([date], 8) or ADDWEEK([date], -3)

[ADDMONTH]
3
Adds / subtracts from the date specified number of months.
Parameters: date, number
Result: date
Example: ADDMONTH([date], 8) or ADDMONTH([date], -3)

[ADDYEAR]
3
Adds / subtracts from the date specified number of years.
Parameters: date, number
Result: date
Example: ADDYEAR([date], 8) or ADDYEAR([date], -3)

[CTIME]
4
Converts a text to time.
Parameters: text
Result: time
Example: CTIME('8:34')

[HOUROF]
5
Extracts from the time of number of hours.
Parameters: time
Result: number
Example: HOUROF([time]). If [time] = 08:23 then function return: 8.

[MINUTEOF]
5
Extracts from the time of number of minutes.
Parameters: time
Result: number
Example: MINUTEOF([time]). If [time] = 08:23 then function return: 23.

[SECONDOF]
5
Extracts from the time of number of seconds.
Parameters: time
Result: number
Example: SECONDOF([time]). If [time] = 08:23:56 then function return: 56.

[HOURSBETWEEN]
5
Returns the time interval in hours.
Parameters: date1, time1, date2, time2
Result: number
Example: HOURSBETWEEN([begin date], [begin time], [end date], [end time]). If you want to know the interval between the time fields, without the use of dates, it is possible to write an expression like this: HOURSBETWEEN([begin date], [begin time], [end date], [end time]).

[MINUTESBETWEEN]
5
Returns the time interval in minutes.
Parameters: date1, time1, date2, time2
Result: number
Example: MINUTESBETWEEN([begin date], [begin time], [end date], [end time]). 

[SECONDSBETWEEN]
5
Returns the time interval in seconds.
Parameters: date1, time1, date2, time2
Result: number
Example: SECONDSBETWEEN([begin date], [begin time], [end date], [end time]). 

[ADDHOUR]
5
Adds / subtracts from the time specified number of hours.
Parameters: date, time, number, date field - text
Return: time
Example: ADDHOUR([begin date], [begin time], [hours], 'end date'). In this example, the expression is evaluated time for the "end time." The result of calculation also changes the "End date". If, for example, "start time" = 23:00, increases by 2 hours, "begin date" = 23.01.2015, the result of "end time" = 01:00, "end date" = 24.01.2015. The fourth parameter can be empty.

[ADDMINUTE]
5
Adds / subtracts from the time specified number of minutes.
Parameters: date, time, number, date field - text
Result: time
Example: ADDMINUTE([begin date], [begin time], [minutes], 'end date').

[ADDSECOND]
5
Adds / subtracts from the time specified number of seconds.
Parameters: date, time, number, date field - text
Result: time
Example: ADDSECOND([begin date], [begin time], [seconds], 'end date').

[PERIOD]
3
NOT IMPLEMENTED! Calculates seniority.
Parameters: date1, date2, format - number
Result: text
Example: PERIOD([begin date], [end date], 3). 

[FDATE]
3
NOT IMPLEMENTED! Returns the date in the format of "January 1, 2009".
Parameters: date
Result: text
Example: FDATE([date])

[NZ]
4
Returns the second argument if the first - NULL.
Parameters: any, any
Result: any
Example: NZ([date], "no date"). Function returns "no date" if [date]=NULL, else - [date].

[INDEXOF]
0
Returns a substring index N.
Parameters: N - number, text
Result: text
Example: INDEXOF(4, "zero;one;two;three;four;five"), function returns "four". The index starts at zero. 

[MERGE]
0
Merges into a single string column values of the table.
Parameters: form name - text, field name - text, delimiter - text
Result: text
Example: MERGE('Bugs', 'Bug', ', ')

[RECID]
4
Returns the record ID (primary key) form.
Parameters: form name - text
Result: number
Example: RECID('clients').
It uses the filter query.

[OBJID]
6
Returns the identifier (primary key) of the object.
Parameters: form name - text, field name - text, value - text
Result: number
Example: OBJID('clients', 'name', 'Ivanon I. I.').
Used in the filter list from the query.

[USER]
4
Returns current user name.
Parameters: none
Result: text

[ROLE]
4
Returns role name of current user.
Parameters: none
Result: text

[DBSUM]
6
Calculates the sum of the values of the field.
Parameters: name of the form - text, the field name - text, filter - text.
Result: The number or NULL (any type)
Example: DBSUM('Sales', 'Sum', '[!Date] <= [date]')
The calculation includes only those records that meet the filter criteria. The syntax is the same as the filter in the filter of source (see. Help topic "Request", "Reports"). The function can be applied to any form of database.

[DBAVG]
6
Calculates the arithmetic mean of the values of the field.
Parameters: name of the form - text, the field name - text, filter - text.
Result: The number or NULL (any type)
Example: DBAVG('Sales', 'Sum', '[!Date] <= [date]')
The calculation includes only those records that meet the filter criteria. The syntax is the same as the filter in the filter of source (see. Help topic "Request", "Reports"). The function can be applied to any form of database.

[DBMAX]
6
Calculates the maximum value of the field.
Parameters: name of the form - text, the field name - text, filter - text.
Result: any type
Example: DBMAX('Sales', 'Sum', '[!Date] <= [date]')
The calculation includes only those records that meet the filter criteria. The syntax is the same as the filter in the filter of source (see. Help topic "Request", "Reports"). The function can be applied to any form of database.

[DBMIN]
6
Calculates the minimum value of the field.
Parameters: name of the form - text, the field name - text, filter - text.
Result: any type
Example: DBMIN('Sales', 'Sum', '[!Date] <= [date]')
The calculation includes only those records that meet the filter criteria. The syntax is the same as the filter in the filter of source (see. Help topic "Request", "Reports"). The function can be applied to any form of database.

[DBCOUNT]
6
Calculates the number of records.
Parameters: name of the form - text, filter - text.
Result: The number or NULL (any type)
Example: DBCOUNT('Sales', 'Sum', '[!Date] <= [date]')
The calculation includes only those records that meet the filter criteria. The syntax is the same as the filter in the filter of source (see. Help topic "Request", "Reports"). The function can be applied to any form of database.

[DBGET]
6
Returns the value of the field.
Parameters: name of the form - text, the field name - text, filter - text.
Result: any type
Example: DBGET('Sales', 'Sum', '[!Date] = [date]')
The database can be several records that match the filter. The function takes the first record. The syntax is the same as the filter in the filter of source (see. Help topic "Request", "Reports"). The function can be applied to any form of database.

[DBGETID]
6
Returns the record ID.
Parameters: name of the form - text, filter - text.
Result: number
Example: DBGET('Sales', '[!Date] = [date]')
The database can be several records that match the filter. The function takes the first record. The syntax is the same as the filter in the filter of source (see. Help topic "Request", "Reports"). The function can be applied to any form of database.

[DBGETBYID]
6
Returns the value of the record with the specified identifier.
Parameters: name of the form - text, the field name - text, id - number.
Result: any type
Example: DBGETBYID('Services', 'Name', DBGETID(...))

[MINV]
2
Returns the minimum value.
Parameters: value1 - any type, value2, ..., valueN
Result: any type
Example: MINV([price1], [price2], [price3])

[MAXV]
2
Returns the maximum value.
Parameters: value1 - any type, value2, ..., valueN
Result: any type
Example: MAXV([price1], [price2], [price3])

[SETVAR]
4
Stores value in the variable.
Parameters: name - text, value - any type
Result: any type
Example: SETVAR('My var', LENGTH([text])
The variable name may contain any characters that are not case sensitive. The function returns a value the second parameter.

[GETVAR]
4
Returns the value of the variable.
Parameters: name - text
Result: any type
Example: GETVAR('My var')
If the variable is not found, the program reports an error.

[IFZ]
4
Returns the second argument if the first is 0.
Parameters: number, any type
Result: any type
Example: IFZ([number], '-')

[IFE]
4
Returns the second argument if the first - empty string.
Parameters: text, any type
Result: any type
Example: IFE([text], '-')

[TRIM]
0
Removes all leading and trailing spaces.
Parameters: text
Result: text
Example: TRIM([text])

[AGE]
3
NOT IMPLEMENTED! Calculates age.
Parameters: date1, date2, format - number
Result: text

[SUMPERIOD]
1
NOT IMPLEMENTED! Calculate the general seniority according to the table.
Parameters: form name - text, begin date field - text, end date field - text, format - number
Result: text

[ZEROS]
0
Adds ahead of zeros.
Parameters: number, text length - number
Result: text
Examples: ZEROS(4, 3), return: 004

[BLOCK]
4
Returns the value of the last argument.
Parameters: value1 - any type, value2, ..., valueN
Result: any type
Example: BLOCK(setvar('var1', 10), setvar('var2', 20), 0)
The purpose of this function to perform some action sequence before the main calculations, for example, to prepare variables.

[VAREXISTS]
4
Returns 1 if variable exists, otherwise 0.
Parameters: variable name - text
Result: number
Example: iif(varexists('my') = 1, setvar('my', getvar('my') + 1), setvar('my', 0))
